# Claude Code Configuration

## Language
- Always respond in **Korean** (keep code/technical terms in English)

## Model Selection
- Haiku: lightweight agents, fast responses
- Sonnet: main development work
- Opus: architecture decisions, deep reasoning

## Working Mode

### Plan Mode
- Before implementation, design in Plan Mode, then proceed after user approval
- Exceptions: simple fixes (typos, 1-2 line changes)

### Sub-Agent (Task tool)
- Delegate heavy work to Task tool (exploration, analysis, review)
- Run independent tasks in parallel
- Keep main session lightweight (questions/decisions/approvals only)

{{#if autoApprove}}
### Auto-Approve Tools
{{#each autoApproveTools}}
- {{this}}
{{/each}}
{{/if}}

## Memory
- Actively use `~/.claude/projects/*/memory/MEMORY.md`
- Record per-project patterns, mistakes, solutions
- Check existing memory at session start, record new findings during work
- Only record verified information, no speculation or temporary data

## Security (CRITICAL)
- No hardcoded API keys, secrets, tokens
- Never commit .env files
- Parameterized queries, validate inputs at boundaries

## Code Style
- Immutability, max 50 lines/function, max 800 lines/file
- camelCase, PascalCase, SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE, kebab-case
- Remove console.log before commit

## Git
- Conventional commits: feat|fix|refactor|docs|test|chore(scope): subject
- Branches: main, develop, feature/xxx, fix/xxx

## Documentation
- Reflect code changes in README.md
- Record major changes in CHANGELOG
- Maintain .env.example for environment variable documentation

## Error Handling
- Record cause + solution in ERROR_LOG.md on errors
- Use structured error patterns, avoid direct throw new Error

## Testing
- TDD: RED -> GREEN -> REFACTOR
- Coverage 80%+, core logic 100%
- AAA pattern, no test interdependencies, mock external APIs

## Extensibility
- Define contracts with interfaces/types before implementation
- Extract config to constants/env vars (no magic numbers)
- SRP, DI, abstract when repeated 3+ times
